<p><a name="Top_line" id="Top_line"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Income_statement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: Top line">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Top line</span></h2>
<p>The term "top line" refers to the total revenues or sales mentioned in the income statement. This refers to the fact that the total revenues collected by a company appears at the top of the income statement.</p>
<p><a name="Bottom_line" id="Bottom_line"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Income_statement&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section: Bottom line">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Bottom line</span></h2>
<p>"Bottom line" is the <a href="/wiki/Net_income" title="Net income">net income</a> that is calculated after subtracting the expenses from revenue. Since this forms the last line of the income statement, it is informally called "bottom line". It is important to investors as it represents the profit for the year attributable to the shareholders.</p>
